{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "SuperFastRateLaws",
        "description": "The five SuperFast rate-law helper functions migrated from GasChem.jl@8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309 src/SuperFast.jl — the reusable builder functions the SuperFast() chemical mechanism uses to construct the rate coefficient of every gas-phase reaction. Each is migrated as its own observed-only algebraic `models` entry: rate_toppb (SuperFast.jl:6) the constant-rate / `constant_k` converter, arrh (:33) the modified-Arrhenius workhorse, arr_3rd (:64) the third-body / Troe-falloff law, rate_2HO2 (:102) the HO2+HO2 law with water-vapour enhancement, and rate_OH_CO (:142) the JPL 15-10 OH+CO law. Upstream each function returns a one-variable ReactionSystem (`@variables k(t)`); the composed builders (arr_3rd, rate_2HO2, rate_OH_CO) compose `arrh` sub-systems. This file reproduces each function's compiled rate as a topologically-ordered cascade of `type: state` algebraic equations whose named intermediates mirror the upstream Julia locals and sub-system k's verbatim, with the Arrhenius coefficients exposed as `type: parameter` (defaults taken from the representative SuperFast reaction each builder serves). All five models are purely algebraic — no time derivatives — so each rate coefficient is constant in time. Units follow the upstream's mixed CGS / ppb system (rate coefficients in 1/(s*ppb), Arrhenius pre-exponentials in cm^3/molec/s).",
        "tags": [
            "gaschem",
            "superfast",
            "rate-laws",
            "reaction-rate",
            "arrhenius",
            "troe-falloff",
            "interface",
            "observed-only",
            "tropospheric-chemistry"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "GasChem.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-d7iu)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Brown-Steiner, B., Selin, N. E., Prinn, R. G., Tilmes, S., Emmons, L., Lamarque, J.-F., & Cameron-Smith, P. (2018). Evaluating simplified chemical mechanisms within present-day simulations of the Community Earth System Model version 1.2 with CAM4 (CESM1.2 CAM-chem): MOZART-4 vs. Reduced Hydrocarbon vs. Super-Fast chemistry. Geoscientific Model Development, 11, 4155-4174. The Super-Fast mechanism whose rate laws these builder functions construct."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Atkinson, R., Baulch, D. L., Cox, R. A., Hampson, R. F., Kerr, J. A., & Troe, J. (1992). Evaluated kinetic and photochemical data for atmospheric chemistry. Journal of Physical and Chemical Reference Data, 21, 1125-1568. Source of the Troe falloff parameterization used by arr_3rd (the fv broadening parameter)."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Sander, S. P., et al. (2011). Chemical Kinetics and Photochemical Data for Use in Atmospheric Studies, Evaluation No. 17 (JPL Publication 10-6). The OH + CO rate parameterization (cf. 'JPL 15-10') reproduced by rate_OH_CO."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "rate_toppb": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: GasChem.jl@8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309:src/SuperFast.jl:6\n\n`rate_toppb(t, T, P, a0)` is the SuperFast constant-rate (a.k.a. `constant_k`) builder: it wraps a temperature-independent reaction rate coefficient a0, supplied in CGS cm^3/molec/s, and converts it to the (s*ppb)^-1 units the SuperFast mechanism's ppb-based species require. It is the rate law used for the single constant-rate SuperFast reaction `cons(4.0e-24, T, P), H2O + NO2 --> 0.5HNO3` (SuperFast.jl:291); the SuperFast() builder calls it through the local `cons` closure, hence the `constant_k` alias in the migration tracker title.\n\nUpstream the function returns a one-variable `ReactionSystem` with `@variables k(t)` and the single equation `k ~ a0 * c`, where `air_volume = R*T/P` and `c = A/air_volume*ppb_unit` are Julia locals. This migration preserves that decomposition explicitly: air_volume and c are `type: state` cascade variables (each defined by one algebraic equation) and k is the `type: state` output. The rate coefficient a0 and the three physical constants A/R/ppb_unit are `type: parameter`. The upstream `@constants` block also declares num_density_unit_inv, which rate_toppb's equation never references; it is omitted here so every declared parameter is load-bearing.\n\nDefault a0 = 4.0e-24 cm^3/molec/s is the coefficient of the only SuperFast reaction that uses this builder (H2O + NO2 --> 0.5HNO3). T = 280 K and P = 101325 Pa are the SuperFast() parameter defaults. At those defaults air_volume = 22974.784110535405 cm^3/mol, c = 26202640125.09021 and k = 1.0481056050036084e-13 (s*ppb)^-1.\n\nAlgebraic, no time derivative: every variable is the LHS of exactly one equation in T, P and the constants, so the trajectory is constant in time (the default test pins k at t=0 and t=1). Tolerance rel=1e-10 is purely relative — the three equations are a handful of IEEE-754 ops each, correctly-rounded to ~1 ULP, and 1e-10 leaves ~5 orders of magnitude of headroom while still catching any coefficient or operator regression. No abs floor is needed: every value is solidly non-zero."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-10
            },
            "variables": {
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 280.0,
                    "description": "Air temperature. Upstream the rate-law builders receive T as a `ParentScope` parameter; the default 280.0 K is the SuperFast() `@parameters T` default (SuperFast.jl:250)."
                },
                "P": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "Pa",
                    "default": 101325.0,
                    "description": "Air pressure. Upstream a `ParentScope` parameter; the default 101325 Pa (1 atm) is the SuperFast() `@parameters P` default (SuperFast.jl:251)."
                },
                "A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "molec/mol",
                    "default": 6.02e+23,
                    "description": "Avogadro's number. Upstream `@constants A = 6.02e23` (SuperFast.jl). Appears in the ppb conversion factor c = A/air_volume*ppb_unit."
                },
                "R": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "(Pa*cm^3)/(K*mol)",
                    "default": 8314000.0,
                    "description": "Universal gas constant in the upstream's mixed Pa-cm^3 unit system. Upstream `@constants R = 8.314e6`. Sets the molar air volume air_volume = R*T/P."
                },
                "ppb_unit": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "ppb",
                    "default": 1e-09,
                    "description": "mol/mol_air -> ppb conversion factor. Upstream `@constants ppb_unit = 1.0e-9`."
                },
                "a0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "cm^3/molec/s",
                    "default": 4e-24,
                    "description": "Constant (temperature-independent) reaction rate coefficient in CGS cm^3/molec/s. Default 4.0e-24 from the SuperFast reaction `H2O + NO2 --> 0.5HNO3` (SuperFast.jl:291)."
                },
                "air_volume": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "cm^3/mol",
                    "description": "Molar volume of air, R*T/P."
                },
                "c": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "molec*ppb/cm^3",
                    "description": "ppb conversion factor A/air_volume*ppb_unit applied to the CGS rate coefficient."
                },
                "k": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1/(s*ppb)",
                    "description": "Reaction rate coefficient in SuperFast (s*ppb)^-1 units: k = a0 * c."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "air_volume",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "R",
                                    "T"
                                ]
                            },
                            "P"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "c",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    "A",
                                    "air_volume"
                                ]
                            },
                            "ppb_unit"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "k",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "a0",
                            "c"
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_h2o_no2_reaction",
                    "description": "All parameters at their defaults: T=280 K, P=101325 Pa, a0=4.0e-24 cm^3/molec/s (the H2O + NO2 --> 0.5HNO3 coefficient). Pins every cascade variable, so any wrong constant or operator is caught. k is asserted at t=0 and t=1 — the model is algebraic with no time derivative, so the trajectory must be exactly constant.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {},
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "air_volume",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 22974.784110535405
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 26202640125.09021
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1.0481056050036084e-13
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": 1.0481056050036084e-13
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "cold_temperature",
                    "description": "T lowered to 250 K with P and a0 at defaults. air_volume = R*T/P falls with T, so the conversion factor c = A/air_volume*ppb_unit rises and k rises proportionally — k is inversely proportional to temperature.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 250.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "air_volume",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 20513.200098692327
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 29346956940.101036
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1.1738782776040414e-13
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "high_pressure",
                    "description": "P raised to 120000 Pa with T and a0 at defaults. air_volume falls with rising P, so c and k both rise — k is linearly proportional to pressure.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "P": 120000.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "air_volume",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 19399.333333333332
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 31031994226.60573
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1.241279769064229e-13
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "rate_coefficient_doubled",
                    "description": "a0 doubled to 8.0e-24 cm^3/molec/s with T and P at defaults. Since k = a0*c and c depends only on T and P, k doubles exactly while air_volume and c are unchanged — confirms a0 is wired as a linear multiplier.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "a0": 8e-24
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 26202640125.09021
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 2.0962112100072168e-13
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "constant_rate_vs_temperature",
                    "description": "Sweeps temperature T from 230 K to 320 K (the tropospheric range) with P and a0 at defaults. The constant-rate builder has no Arrhenius factor, so the only temperature dependence is through c = A*P/(R*T)*ppb_unit: k falls as 1/T across the sweep.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "T",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 230.0,
                                    "stop": 320.0,
                                    "count": 60,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "constant_rate_k_vs_t",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Converted constant rate coefficient k versus temperature — a smooth 1/T decay.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "T",
                                "label": "Temperature (K)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "k",
                                "label": "Rate coefficient k (1/(s*ppb))"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "arrh": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: GasChem.jl@8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309:src/SuperFast.jl:33\n\n`arrh(t, T, P, a0, b0, c0)` is the SuperFast modified-Arrhenius rate builder. It is the workhorse rate law of the SuperFast mechanism: most of the ~20 gas-phase reactions in SuperFast() are built with it (through the local `arr` closure), and the three other builders in this file (arr_3rd, rate_2HO2, rate_OH_CO) all compose arrh sub-systems internally.\n\nThe compiled equation is `k ~ a0 * exp(c0/T) * (K_300/T)^b0 * c`, with `air_volume = R*T/P` and `c = A/air_volume*ppb_unit` as Julia locals. NOTE the exponent base: the source CODE uses (K_300/T)^b0 = (300/T)^b0, whereas the function's docstring writes (T/300)^b0 — the code is authoritative and is what every SuperFast reaction actually uses, so this migration transcribes (K_300/T)^b0. air_volume and c are `type: state` cascade variables; k is the `type: state` output. a0/b0/c0 and A/R/ppb_unit/K_300 are `type: parameter`; the unused upstream `@constants num_density_unit_inv` is omitted.\n\nDefaults a0 = 1.7e-12 cm^3/molec/s, b0 = 0 (dimensionless), c0 = -940 K are the coefficients of the first SuperFast reaction, `arr(T, P, 1.7e-12, 0.0, -940.0), O3 + OH --> HO2 + O2` (SuperFast.jl:275). With b0 = 0 the (K_300/T)^b0 factor is exactly 1.0; the b0_nonzero test exercises a non-trivial power-law factor and the o3_no_reaction_coefficients test swaps in a second real SuperFast coefficient set. At the defaults k = 0.0015516914092470017 (s*ppb)^-1.\n\nAlgebraic, no time derivative. Tolerance rel=1e-10, purely relative: the equation adds one exp and one pow to the rate_toppb expression tree; both are correctly-rounded library calls and 1e-10 absorbs any libm/numpy ULP-level difference while still pinning a0, b0, c0 and the (K_300/T) base to full working precision."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-10
            },
            "variables": {
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 280.0,
                    "description": "Air temperature. Upstream the rate-law builders receive T as a `ParentScope` parameter; the default 280.0 K is the SuperFast() `@parameters T` default (SuperFast.jl:250)."
                },
                "P": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "Pa",
                    "default": 101325.0,
                    "description": "Air pressure. Upstream a `ParentScope` parameter; the default 101325 Pa (1 atm) is the SuperFast() `@parameters P` default (SuperFast.jl:251)."
                },
                "A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "molec/mol",
                    "default": 6.02e+23,
                    "description": "Avogadro's number. Upstream `@constants A = 6.02e23` (SuperFast.jl). Appears in the ppb conversion factor c = A/air_volume*ppb_unit."
                },
                "R": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "(Pa*cm^3)/(K*mol)",
                    "default": 8314000.0,
                    "description": "Universal gas constant in the upstream's mixed Pa-cm^3 unit system. Upstream `@constants R = 8.314e6`. Sets the molar air volume air_volume = R*T/P."
                },
                "ppb_unit": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "ppb",
                    "default": 1e-09,
                    "description": "mol/mol_air -> ppb conversion factor. Upstream `@constants ppb_unit = 1.0e-9`."
                },
                "K_300": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 300.0,
                    "description": "Arrhenius reference temperature (300 K). Upstream `@constants K_300 = 300`."
                },
                "a0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "cm^3/molec/s",
                    "default": 1.7e-12,
                    "description": "Arrhenius pre-exponential factor in CGS cm^3/molec/s. Default 1.7e-12 from `O3 + OH --> HO2 + O2` (SuperFast.jl:275)."
                },
                "b0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Arrhenius power-law (temperature) exponent for the (K_300/T)^b0 factor. Default 0.0 (no power-law dependence) from `O3 + OH --> HO2 + O2`."
                },
                "c0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": -940.0,
                    "description": "Arrhenius activation-temperature parameter (-Ea/R) in K for the exp(c0/T) factor. Default -940.0 from `O3 + OH --> HO2 + O2`."
                },
                "air_volume": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "cm^3/mol",
                    "description": "Molar volume of air, R*T/P."
                },
                "c": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "molec*ppb/cm^3",
                    "description": "ppb conversion factor A/air_volume*ppb_unit."
                },
                "k": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1/(s*ppb)",
                    "description": "Modified-Arrhenius rate coefficient in (s*ppb)^-1: k = a0*exp(c0/T)*(K_300/T)^b0*c."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "air_volume",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "R",
                                    "T"
                                ]
                            },
                            "P"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "c",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    "A",
                                    "air_volume"
                                ]
                            },
                            "ppb_unit"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": "k",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "a0",
                            {
                                "op": "exp",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            "c0",
                                            "T"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "^",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            "K_300",
                                            "T"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "b0"
                                ]
                            },
                            "c"
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_o3_oh_reaction",
                    "description": "All parameters at their defaults: T=280 K, P=101325 Pa, a0=1.7e-12, b0=0.0, c0=-940.0 (the O3 + OH --> HO2 + O2 coefficient set). With b0=0 the (K_300/T)^b0 power-law factor is exactly 1.0. Pins every cascade variable; k asserted at t=0 and t=1 for time-invariance.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {},
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "air_volume",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 22974.784110535405
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 26202640125.09021
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.0015516914092470017
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 1.0,
                            "expected": 0.0015516914092470017
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "warm_temperature",
                    "description": "T raised to 300 K. Both the exp(c0/T) Arrhenius factor and the conversion factor c shift with temperature; the test pins the combined result.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "T": 300.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "air_volume",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 24615.84011843079
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "c",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 24455797450.084198
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.0018115126600967313
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "nonzero_power_law_exponent",
                    "description": "b0 set to 2.0 with all else at defaults, activating the (K_300/T)^b0 power-law factor. At T=280 K, K_300/T = 300/280 > 1, so (K_300/T)^2 > 1 and k is larger than the b0=0 default.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "b0": 2.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.0017812784034723233
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "zero_activation_temperature",
                    "description": "c0 set to 0.0, so the exp(c0/T) factor collapses to exp(0)=1.0 and k reduces to a0*(K_300/T)^b0*c. With the default b0=0 this is just a0*c = the rate_toppb form — k jumps by exactly the factor 1/exp(-940/280) relative to the default.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "c0": 0.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.04454448821265336
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "o3_no_reaction_coefficients",
                    "description": "A second real SuperFast coefficient set: a0=3.0e-12, b0=0.0, c0=-1500.0, the O3 + NO --> NO2 + O2 reaction (SuperFast.jl:280). Exercises arrh with a different pre-exponential and a stronger (more negative) activation temperature.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "a0": 3e-12,
