                            "variable": "xyrat",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 2.071806522801997
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "fexp",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.9090274310086746
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "k",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.4948327341058403
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "third_body_rate_vs_pressure",
                    "description": "Sweeps pressure P from 20000 Pa to 101325 Pa (upper troposphere to surface) with the default NO2+OH coefficients. num_density_unitless is proportional to P, so the low-pressure branch and the falloff ratio xyrat both strengthen with pressure — the defining behaviour of a third-body / falloff rate law.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "P",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 20000.0,
                                    "stop": 101325.0,
                                    "count": 60,
                                    "scale": "linear"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "third_body_k_vs_p",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Third-body rate coefficient k versus pressure — k climbs as the low-pressure branch fills in.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "P",
                                "label": "Pressure (Pa)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "k",
                                "label": "Rate coefficient k (1/(s*ppb))"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "falloff_ratio_vs_p",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Falloff ratio xyrat = rlow/rhigh versus pressure, showing the transition between the low- and high-pressure limits.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "P",
                                "label": "Pressure (Pa)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "xyrat",
                                "label": "Falloff ratio xyrat (dimensionless)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "rate_2HO2": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: GasChem.jl@8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309:src/SuperFast.jl:102\n\n`rate_2HO2(t, T, P, H2O, a0, c0, a1, c1)` is the SuperFast rate builder for `HO2 + HO2 --> H2O2 + O2` (SuperFast.jl:278). It sums a bimolecular channel and a termolecular (number-density-scaled) channel and multiplies by a water-vapour enhancement factor.\n\nUpstream it composes two b0=0 `arrh` sub-systems (`k0`, `k1`) and uses the Julia locals num_density_unitless and H2O_ppb_molec_cm3:\n  num_density_unitless = A*P/(R*T)*num_density_unit_inv\n  H2O_ppb_molec_cm3    = H2O*ppb_inv*1.0e-9*num_density_unitless\n  k0.k = arrh(a0,0.0,c0) ; k1.k = arrh(a1,0.0,c1)\n  k    = (k0.k + k1.k*num_density_unitless)\n         * (1 + 1.4e-21*H2O*H2O_ppb_molec_cm3*exp(T_0/T))\nThis migration reproduces each named quantity as a `type: state` cascade variable: air_volume, c, num_density_unitless, H2O_ppb_molec_cm3, the two sub-arrh outputs k0_k and k1_k, and the output k — seven equations. Both sub-arrh calls fix b0=0, so the (K_300/T)^0.0 factor is written verbatim and evaluates to exactly 1.0. The water-enhancement term is transcribed exactly as upstream writes it, including H2O appearing both as the raw ppb value and (via H2O_ppb_molec_cm3) as a number density — this product shape is preserved verbatim from the source, not 'corrected'.\n\nDefaults H2O=1.839e7 ppb (the SuperFast() `@parameters H2O` default, SuperFast.jl:254), a0=3.0e-13, c0=460.0, a1=2.1e-33, c1=920.0 (the HO2+HO2 coefficient set, SuperFast.jl:278). At T=280 K, P=101325 Pa the water-enhancement factor is ~3.2e7, so k = 2538324.212508474 (s*ppb)^-1; with H2O=0 the factor collapses to exactly 1.0 and k = 0.07917658137395685 (the bare k0_k + k1_k*num_density_unitless sum). The h2o_zero test pins both that k and H2O_ppb_molec_cm3 = 0.0 exactly.\n\nAlgebraic, no time derivative. Tolerance rel=1e-10, purely relative: relative tolerance handles the ~8-orders-of-magnitude spread between the small k1_k channel and the large k. The single exact-zero assertion (H2O_ppb_molec_cm3 at H2O=0) is bit-exactly 0.0 because 0.0*x = 0.0 in IEEE-754, so it passes the runner's exact-match path with no abs floor required."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-10
            },
            "variables": {
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 280.0,
                    "description": "Air temperature. Upstream the rate-law builders receive T as a `ParentScope` parameter; the default 280.0 K is the SuperFast() `@parameters T` default (SuperFast.jl:250)."
                },
                "P": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "Pa",
                    "default": 101325.0,
                    "description": "Air pressure. Upstream a `ParentScope` parameter; the default 101325 Pa (1 atm) is the SuperFast() `@parameters P` default (SuperFast.jl:251)."
                },
                "A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "molec/mol",
                    "default": 6.02e+23,
                    "description": "Avogadro's number. Upstream `@constants A = 6.02e23` (SuperFast.jl). Appears in the ppb conversion factor c = A/air_volume*ppb_unit."
                },
                "R": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "(Pa*cm^3)/(K*mol)",
                    "default": 8314000.0,
                    "description": "Universal gas constant in the upstream's mixed Pa-cm^3 unit system. Upstream `@constants R = 8.314e6`. Sets the molar air volume air_volume = R*T/P."
                },
                "ppb_unit": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "ppb",
                    "default": 1e-09,
                    "description": "mol/mol_air -> ppb conversion factor. Upstream `@constants ppb_unit = 1.0e-9`."
                },
                "num_density_unit_inv": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "cm^3/molec",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Unit-stripping factor that turns the air number density into the dimensionless num_density_unitless. Upstream `@constants num_density_unit_inv = 1`."
                },
                "ppb_inv": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1/ppb",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Unit-stripping factor (ppb^-1). Upstream `@constants ppb_inv = 1`."
                },
                "K_300": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 300.0,
                    "description": "Arrhenius reference temperature (300 K). Upstream `@constants K_300 = 300`."
                },
                "T_0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 2200.0,
                    "description": "Characteristic temperature of the HO2+HO2 water-vapour enhancement term. Upstream `@constants T_0 = 2200.0`."
                },
                "H2O": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "ppb",
                    "default": 18390000.0,
                    "description": "Water-vapour mixing ratio in ppb. Default 1.839e7 ppb (~1.8%) is the SuperFast() `@parameters H2O` default (SuperFast.jl:254)."
                },
                "a0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "cm^3/molec/s",
                    "default": 3e-13,
                    "description": "Bimolecular-channel Arrhenius pre-exponential. Default 3.0e-13 from `HO2 + HO2 --> H2O2 + O2` (SuperFast.jl:278)."
                },
                "c0": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 460.0,
                    "description": "Bimolecular-channel activation-temperature parameter. Default 460.0."
                },
                "a1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "cm^3/molec/s",
                    "default": 2.1e-33,
                    "description": "Termolecular-channel Arrhenius pre-exponential. Default 2.1e-33 from `HO2 + HO2 --> H2O2 + O2`."
                },
                "c1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 920.0,
                    "description": "Termolecular-channel activation-temperature parameter. Default 920.0."
                },
                "air_volume": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "cm^3/mol",
                    "description": "Molar volume of air, R*T/P."
                },
                "c": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "molec*ppb/cm^3",
                    "description": "ppb conversion factor A/air_volume*ppb_unit."
                },
                "num_density_unitless": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Dimensionless air number density A*P/(R*T)*num_density_unit_inv."
                },
                "H2O_ppb_molec_cm3": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Water-vapour concentration converted from ppb toward a molec/cm^3 number density, H2O*ppb_inv*1.0e-9*num_density_unitless."
                },
                "k0_k": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1/(s*ppb)",
                    "description": "Bimolecular HO2+HO2 channel (arrh with a0,0,c0)."
                },
                "k1_k": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1/(s*ppb)",
                    "description": "Termolecular HO2+HO2 channel base rate (arrh with a1,0,c1), scaled by num_density_unitless in k."
                },
                "k": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1/(s*ppb)",
                    "description": "HO2+HO2 rate coefficient including the water-vapour enhancement factor."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
